^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
--> Before injecting any substance into your lips, your provider may administer a topical anesthetic or dental block to increase comfort during the procedure.

Aftercare & Recovery
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
--> After the procedure, you may experience slight swelling, sensitivity, or bruising on the treated area.
--> You can use an ice pack on your lips for 10 minutes fto reduce inflammation.
--> Avoid wearing make-up products or lip balms for at least 24 hours after the procedure.
--> Patients will require maintenance treatments every three to six months to maintain optimal results.

Am I a Good Candidate?
----------------------
Anyone interested in enhancing their lips’ appearance and not allergic to the ingredients is a good candidate for lip filler. However, the ideal candidate for this procedure is overall in good health, doesn’t smoke, and is committed to maintaining good skin health.

--> Fat Grafting: Fat Grafting is a long-lasting surgical procedure for your lips. A small amount of fat is taken from a donor site on the body, then injected into your lips.

Lip Filler for Men Side Effects & Risks
---------------------------------------
As with any procedure requiring injection, bruising and swelling are common side effects but will subside in the following days; some side effects also depend on the individual’s response to the treatment. Risks and side effects may include
--> Bleeding
--> Redness
--> reactivation of cold sores or fever blisters
--> lip asymmetry
--> lumps/bumps
--> Infection

Lip Filler for Men FAQs
-----------------------

How long will the filler last men?
""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
Lip filler for men will usually last from three months to twelve months. The filter will gradually break down, and the body will absorb it. The duration of results depends on the individual’s metabolism, the type of filler used, and the amount of filler injected.

Is it common for males to get lip fillers?
""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
Yes, lip fillers are as beneficial for men as they are for women. It is becoming increasingly common for men to get lip filler for a fresh, more youthful appearance. As ladies look for a fuller and more voluminous lip look, men tend to desire a more natural look.

How much does lip filler for men cost?
""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
The average cost in the United States varies from $500-$2,000. There are plenty of cosmetic options available for any budget. The price will vary based on the desired goal, the type of filler used, and how much filler is required. Our pricing is highly competitive when compared to the national average.

Does lip filler hurt?
"""""""""""""""""""""
The procedure should cause minimal pain or discomfort. Your provider may apply the topical anesthetic or full dental block to help to ease any pain. However, because the lips are the most sensitive area of the face, some level of pain is to be expected.

What is the Russian lip filler technique?
"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
The Russian technique involves accentuating the Cupid’s bow to resemble a heart shape by injecting more filler in the center of the lip. This technique gives a fuller and plumper lip look.

How often can I get lip filler?
"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
You can repeat the lip filler treatment every six months, but it differs from person to person. Hyaluronic acid injected into your lip helps produce collagen, which helps to create more plumped and defined lips. However, it is up to you and your desired outcome.

What is a macho mouth?
""""""""""""""""""""""
The ratio of the lips is different in men than in women. Women have a one-third to two-thirds ratio, upper lip to lower lip; in men, the ratio is closer to one-fourth to three-fourths. Men’s lip shape also differs; the upper lip is generally flatter and has less of a cupid’s bow. These slight differences make a lip more masculine or feminine.

Do straight guys get lip injections?
""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
Yes! Kissable lips never go out of style and are in no way dependent upon sexual orientation or gender. All genders can both enjoy kissable and fuller lips.

Can you get lip fillers in one lip?
"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
Yes. If you want a more modest lip enhancement, fillers in one lip may be the perfect solution. Filler treatments provide natural-looking results and are highly customizable to cater to your specific needs and goals.
